1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:02,269
Netero: Wait.

2
00:00:03,570 --> 00:00:06,907
Exchanging words?

3
00:00:10,544 --> 00:00:12,079
Hey, king...

4
00:00:13,514 --> 00:00:17,184
Would you like
to know your name?

5
00:00:19,353 --> 00:00:23,557
King: How is it that you have
come into possession of my name?

6
00:00:29,296 --> 00:00:31,131
Netero: Simple, really.

7
00:00:31,198 --> 00:00:34,168
My subordinates were present
at your mother’s deathbed.

8
00:00:36,236 --> 00:00:40,307
She uttered your name
with her dying breath.

9
00:00:40,374 --> 00:00:41,942
I bet i’m the only one

10
00:00:42,009 --> 00:00:45,112
who knows now those
same subordinates probably died

11
00:00:45,179 --> 00:00:46,714
fighting your royal guard.

12
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:48,715
( Wind blowing )

13
00:00:52,686 --> 00:00:55,522
Are you interested
in fighting me now?

14
00:00:58,692 --> 00:01:00,294
I’ll make you a deal.

15
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:02,929
If you can force me
to admit defeat,

16
00:01:02,996 --> 00:01:05,432
i’ll tell you your name.

17
00:01:08,135 --> 00:01:09,336
King: Force you?

18
00:01:09,403 --> 00:01:11,105
But without killing you?

19
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:13,073
( Scoffs )

20
00:01:13,140 --> 00:01:15,442
♪

21
00:01:17,144 --> 00:01:20,247
So i’ll be playing
without a rook and bishop.

22
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,270
Fine, then.

23
00:01:43,337 --> 00:01:45,673
I’ll checkmate you shortly.

24
00:02:09,663 --> 00:02:10,597
♪

25
00:02:10,664 --> 00:02:12,599
( Singing in Japanese )

26
00:02:54,308 --> 00:02:56,243
♪

27
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:07,521
Narrator: As the king
and netero prepared

28
00:03:07,588 --> 00:03:11,258
for what they were both certain
would be their final battle...

29
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:15,195
♪

30
00:03:38,585 --> 00:03:42,589
Ikalgo continued to cry
deep beneath the palace,

31
00:03:42,656 --> 00:03:45,626
devastated he had failed
to finish off bloster

32
00:03:45,692 --> 00:03:48,128
even as he lay unconscious.

33
00:03:48,195 --> 00:03:50,130
( Ikalgo weeping )

34
00:04:14,721 --> 00:04:16,656
( Softly crying )

35
00:04:36,643 --> 00:04:38,512
This is the best option.

36
00:04:40,047 --> 00:04:43,183
There’s no one else
to help me.

37
00:04:44,251 --> 00:04:46,153
I have to do this.

38
00:04:47,654 --> 00:04:49,689
I have to!

39
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:51,358
( Gags )

40
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:58,031
This is no time for tears.

41
00:04:58,098 --> 00:04:59,900
I have to find palm.

42
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:00,901
( Gasps )

43
00:05:02,169 --> 00:05:04,872
The door to the warehouse area
is open.

44
00:05:05,973 --> 00:05:07,541
So’s the door to the garage.

45
00:05:07,608 --> 00:05:09,310
Why?

46
00:05:09,376 --> 00:05:10,644
Welfin: Don’t move!

47
00:05:10,711 --> 00:05:11,946
( Ikalgo gasps )

48
00:05:15,015 --> 00:05:17,317
Welfin: If you do, i’ll attack.

49
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:22,555
Ikalgo: Welfin.

50
00:05:22,623 --> 00:05:26,560
Welfin: I’ve got a lot
of questions I wanna ask you,

51
00:05:26,627 --> 00:05:28,963
but if you try anything funny,

52
00:05:29,029 --> 00:05:31,131
you’re dead.

53
00:05:32,366 --> 00:05:34,468
Ikalgo: I’ve got
a pretty good idea

54
00:05:34,535 --> 00:05:36,370
about what he wants to know--

55
00:05:36,436 --> 00:05:39,072
the number of my allies,

56
00:05:39,139 --> 00:05:42,175
their roles,
and their abilities.

57
00:05:42,242 --> 00:05:46,346
And he’ll use any means
necessary to find out.

58
00:05:48,115 --> 00:05:51,452
If I start leaking information,
people could die.

59
00:05:53,187 --> 00:05:54,689
But if he’s a manipulator,

60
00:05:54,755 --> 00:05:58,259
he can obtain the information
against my will.

61
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:02,963
Welfin: Huh? Stop right there.

62
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:04,431
I really will kill you!

63
00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:06,066
Ikalgo: Kill me, then.

64
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,234
That’s what I want.

65
00:06:07,301 --> 00:06:08,636
Welfin: Stop now!

66
00:06:08,702 --> 00:06:10,637
Ikalgo: I won’t betray
my friends,

67
00:06:10,704 --> 00:06:12,940
but i’ll take you with me!

68
00:06:13,006 --> 00:06:14,941
( Welfin wails )

69
00:06:15,008 --> 00:06:17,344
Now you’ve done it,
you bastard!

70
00:06:17,411 --> 00:06:18,946
Damn it!

71
00:06:19,012 --> 00:06:20,914
Fine.

72
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:22,382
Missileman!

73
00:06:22,449 --> 00:06:23,383
( Ikalgo winces )

74
00:06:27,621 --> 00:06:29,356
( Groans )

75
00:06:29,423 --> 00:06:31,926
Hey, i’m not dead.

76
00:06:31,992 --> 00:06:34,595
I didn’t sustain any damage.

77
00:06:34,661 --> 00:06:36,997
What was that attack?

78
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:38,332
Welfin: Ah, damn it.

79
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,200
That really hurts.

80
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:42,302
Why, you little punk.

81
00:06:42,369 --> 00:06:45,005
You’ll pay for this.

82
00:06:45,072 --> 00:06:47,341
That bastard.

83
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:51,211
How did a wimp like that
figure out my weakness?

84
00:06:51,278 --> 00:06:54,281
Missileman needs
questions and answer to work.

85
00:06:54,348 --> 00:06:57,484
If an enemy attacks
before I can ask a question,

86
00:06:57,551 --> 00:06:59,219
it’s null and void.

87
00:06:59,286 --> 00:07:01,555
The wound isn’t deep.

88
00:07:01,622 --> 00:07:03,057
( Laughs )

89
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:06,059
I’ll take my time
beating him to a pulp.

90
00:07:12,332 --> 00:07:14,434
( Ikalgo groaning )

91
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:23,477
( Welfin chuckles )

92
00:07:23,544 --> 00:07:27,481
Ikalgo: Wait. He planted
something living inside me?

93
00:07:27,548 --> 00:07:29,083
- ( Crunch )
- ( Groans )

94
00:07:29,149 --> 00:07:31,018
Welfin: You see that?

95
00:07:31,084 --> 00:07:32,953
The creatures I placed in you

96
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:35,456
are black centipedes
created by nen.

97
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:43,096
They grow by feeding
on your defiance, so get ready.

98
00:07:43,163 --> 00:07:44,665
( Ikalgo groaning )

99
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:52,440
Welfin: If you
disobey my orders

100
00:07:52,506 --> 00:07:55,909
or if you try to harm me
in any way,

101
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:58,912
they will inflict on you
the most excruciating pain,

102
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:02,115
then burst through your body,
killing you!

103
00:08:06,053 --> 00:08:07,421
( Ikalgo groans )

104
00:08:10,324 --> 00:08:11,458
Welfin: Huh?

105
00:08:11,525 --> 00:08:13,594
Hey, what are you doing, idiot?!

106
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:15,929
Didn’t you listen
to a word I just said?!

107
00:08:15,996 --> 00:08:18,532
If you try what I think
you’re going to try...

108
00:08:18,599 --> 00:08:21,135
( Ikalgo groaning )

109
00:08:24,638 --> 00:08:27,574
( Welfin gasping )

110
00:08:27,641 --> 00:08:30,310
Ikalgo: All that’s fine by me.

111
00:08:30,377 --> 00:08:33,380
And if I die, so be it.

112
00:08:33,447 --> 00:08:36,984
( Inhales )

113
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:38,351
Welfin: Ahh! No!

114
00:08:38,418 --> 00:08:39,352
No, stop!

115
00:08:47,194 --> 00:08:48,595
( Thinking )
Wait a minute.

116
00:08:48,662 --> 00:08:51,298
If he wanted to kill me,

117
00:08:51,365 --> 00:08:54,034
that’s the ultimate form
of resistance.

118
00:08:54,101 --> 00:08:56,403
Now it’ll take no time at all

119
00:08:56,470 --> 00:09:00,007
for the black centipedes to grow
large enough to kill him.

120
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:05,546
( Screams )

121
00:09:05,612 --> 00:09:08,315
Ikalgo: Oh, don’t worry.

122
00:09:08,382 --> 00:09:10,517
I won’t kill you.

123
00:09:10,584 --> 00:09:14,188
I just need to make sure
you stay put.

124
00:09:16,623 --> 00:09:19,960
I still have ammunition.

125
00:09:20,027 --> 00:09:21,962
♪

126
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:26,166
Welfin: Don’t mess
with me, bastard!

127
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:27,367
You are so dead.

128
00:09:27,434 --> 00:09:28,969
I’ll kill you, you hear me!

129
00:09:29,036 --> 00:09:31,539
- ( Ikalgo inhales )
- ( Welfin screaming )

130
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,943
( Screaming )

131
00:09:38,045 --> 00:09:39,980
( Ikalgo groaning )

132
00:09:41,048 --> 00:09:43,984
( Centipedes clattering )

133
00:09:44,051 --> 00:09:45,519
( Ikalgo laughing )

134
00:09:45,586 --> 00:09:46,520
Welfin: Huh?

135
00:09:54,495 --> 00:09:56,964
Ikalgo: It’s so easy.

136
00:10:02,436 --> 00:10:04,605
Pulling the trigger
is a breeze...

137
00:10:06,073 --> 00:10:10,110
When the only price
is my life.

138
00:10:18,685 --> 00:10:20,620
♪

139
00:10:24,691 --> 00:10:26,626
( Centipedes rustling )

140
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:32,599
( Welfin whimpers )

141
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:36,203
( Ikalgo inhaling )

142
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:40,640
♪

143
00:10:52,719 --> 00:10:54,654
Welfin: I get it, okay?!

144
00:10:54,721 --> 00:10:57,224
Look, I won’t go anywhere!
I promise!

145
00:11:00,127 --> 00:11:02,963
I give up,
so, please, don’t shoot.

146
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:08,435
Ikalgo: The pain is going away.

147
00:11:08,502 --> 00:11:11,605
The creatures inside me
are in agony?

148
00:11:11,672 --> 00:11:14,408
Welfin: Damn it. You win.

149
00:11:14,474 --> 00:11:17,978
I can’t move anymore.

150
00:11:19,613 --> 00:11:22,983
Ikalgo: I wonder if it’s
because welfin admitted defeat?

151
00:11:27,688 --> 00:11:29,356
Welfin: I saw it coming.

152
00:11:29,423 --> 00:11:33,394
I just had a feeling
this would happen eventually.

153
00:11:35,596 --> 00:11:40,000
But, still, I had no idea
I was this weak.

154
00:11:40,067 --> 00:11:43,504
I didn’t think it’d be
so scary to fight someone

155
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:46,506
who didn’t have any regard
for their own life.

156
00:11:47,608 --> 00:11:48,976
Ikalgo: Welfin.

157
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:50,243
Welfin: What?

158
00:11:50,310 --> 00:11:52,579
Ikalgo: The pain’s
completely subsided,

159
00:11:52,646 --> 00:11:55,449
so do you think you could
get rid of all these bugs now?

160
00:11:55,516 --> 00:11:56,550
( Welfin groans )

161
00:11:56,617 --> 00:11:58,385
Shut the hell up.

162
00:11:58,452 --> 00:12:01,889
I’m in too much pain
to think about that right now.

163
00:12:04,258 --> 00:12:05,826
Ikalgo: Hmm?

164
00:12:05,893 --> 00:12:06,994
( Groans )

165
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,194
Welfin: Uh...

166
00:12:08,262 --> 00:12:09,864
Ikalgo: Hurry up, will you?

167
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:12,399
Welfin: Just give me a minute.

168
00:12:12,466 --> 00:12:17,404
Damn, I don’t have a way
to deactivate missileman,

169
00:12:17,471 --> 00:12:22,009
but if I tell him the truth,
i’m in real trouble.

170
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:24,611
How am I gonna get out of this?

171
00:12:24,678 --> 00:12:27,614
♪

172
00:12:27,681 --> 00:12:29,950
I need to buy some time.

173
00:12:30,017 --> 00:12:33,120
I just need to come up
with a good idea.

174
00:12:35,088 --> 00:12:36,856
( Moans )

175
00:12:36,924 --> 00:12:37,992
Uhh! Pain!

176
00:12:38,058 --> 00:12:40,294
I feel so...( Moans )

177
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,396
Very faint.

178
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:50,236
- ( Centipedes rustling )
- ( Ikalgo growls )

179
00:12:54,508 --> 00:12:55,442
( Welfin winces )

180
00:12:55,509 --> 00:12:57,644
( Moans )

181
00:13:02,049 --> 00:13:03,851
( Gasps ) Whahh!

182
00:13:03,917 --> 00:13:05,352
Hold on! I was kidding!

183
00:13:05,419 --> 00:13:07,121
I’m sorry! ( Winces )

184
00:13:07,187 --> 00:13:10,323
Ikalgo: Then hurry up,
and get rid of these things.

185
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:11,591
( Welfin chuckles )

186
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:13,994
Well, I, um...

187
00:13:14,061 --> 00:13:15,329
Ikalgo: Hmm?

188
00:13:17,064 --> 00:13:20,000
( Welfin groans )

189
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:22,369
Ikalgo: Oh, well. Forget it.

190
00:13:22,436 --> 00:13:24,905
Welfin: No, wait!
Hold on a minute!

191
00:13:24,972 --> 00:13:29,076
I can’t remove them now,
not once they’ve been activated.

192
00:13:32,179 --> 00:13:34,882
Sorry, but it’s true.

193
00:13:34,948 --> 00:13:37,350
I’m not lying!
You gotta believe me!

194
00:13:37,417 --> 00:13:39,286
I swear i’m not
trying to trick you!

195
00:13:41,288 --> 00:13:44,224
Ikalgo: The insects
are in pain again.

196
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:47,327
Is it because
he’s telling the truth?

197
00:13:47,394 --> 00:13:49,396
Welfin: Can you really blame me?

198
00:13:49,463 --> 00:13:53,467
Thing is, I only attack
to kill someone,

199
00:13:53,534 --> 00:13:55,336
and screw what happens next.

200
00:13:55,402 --> 00:13:58,038
I never gave a single thought

201
00:13:58,105 --> 00:14:00,941
to what happened
to my enemy afterwards.

202
00:14:01,008 --> 00:14:05,246
( Chuckles ) Nen abilities
are really something, huh?

203
00:14:05,312 --> 00:14:09,049
My personality is reflected
in my ability.

204
00:14:10,317 --> 00:14:11,585
Ikalgo: "My personality"?

205
00:14:11,652 --> 00:14:14,054
As in his true intentions?

206
00:14:15,155 --> 00:14:16,490
Welfin.

207
00:14:16,557 --> 00:14:18,059
Welfin: Huh?

208
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:21,595
Ikalgo: What do I ask him?

209
00:14:21,662 --> 00:14:23,898
What do I want to know?

210
00:14:23,964 --> 00:14:25,432
Welfin: Huh?

211
00:14:27,401 --> 00:14:31,005
Ikalgo: I once knew
someone just like him.

212
00:14:31,071 --> 00:14:32,873
I’m curious.

213
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:36,076
Do you have any memories
from when you were human?

214
00:14:36,143 --> 00:14:39,446
Welfin: Eh?
Why do you wanna know that?

215
00:14:39,513 --> 00:14:41,181
I can’t remember anything.

216
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:45,452
( Centipedes rustling )

217
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:46,520
Ikalgo: You’re lying.

218
00:14:46,587 --> 00:14:47,621
( Welfin yells )

219
00:14:47,688 --> 00:14:49,256
What are you talking about?

220
00:14:49,323 --> 00:14:52,026
Hold on! Let’s just
talk this over, all right?

221
00:14:52,092 --> 00:14:56,630
Ikalgo: If you don’t tell me
the truth right now, i’ll shoot.

222
00:14:56,697 --> 00:14:58,365
( Welfin gasps )

223
00:14:58,432 --> 00:15:01,201
( Groans )

224
00:15:04,638 --> 00:15:06,840
♪

225
00:15:06,907 --> 00:15:08,876
Fine. You win.

226
00:15:08,942 --> 00:15:13,180
When I woke up,
my first thought was...

227
00:15:13,247 --> 00:15:16,550
( Ikalgo sighs )

228
00:15:17,885 --> 00:15:19,420
Welfin: Aw, damn it.

229
00:15:19,486 --> 00:15:23,490
I still remember it
like it was yesterday.

230
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:27,060
( Automatic weapons firing )

231
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:36,136
Those monster bugs killed me
in the ngl.

232
00:15:36,203 --> 00:15:38,372
I’m sure of it.

233
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:40,140
( Yunju slurps )

234
00:15:47,614 --> 00:15:49,216
Welfin: I was fed to the queen.

235
00:15:49,283 --> 00:15:53,454
And soon I was reborn
as something new.

236
00:15:57,224 --> 00:16:01,795
Even now I can still remember
the one thing that--

237
00:16:01,862 --> 00:16:04,531
that I most wanted to forget...

238
00:16:09,236 --> 00:16:12,106
The sight of my father
strangling me

239
00:16:12,172 --> 00:16:16,109
and the woman behind him
just watching.

240
00:16:20,314 --> 00:16:23,951
In the beginning, I only had
little flashbacks of it,

241
00:16:24,017 --> 00:16:27,554
but over time, I remembered
everything that happened.

242
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:34,361
My little brother saved me...

243
00:16:35,929 --> 00:16:38,165
Even though
we weren’t related by blood.

244
00:16:41,468 --> 00:16:43,370
I remember now!

245
00:16:44,471 --> 00:16:46,039
He looked just like...

246
00:16:46,106 --> 00:16:47,908
Gyro does!

247
00:16:47,975 --> 00:16:50,311
( Ikalgo gasps ) Gyro?

248
00:16:50,377 --> 00:16:52,880
Welfin: You know him
as the king.

249
00:16:56,049 --> 00:16:59,920
We used to fight
about whose life was worse.

250
00:17:01,355 --> 00:17:04,925
When I had to laugh
to keep from crying,

251
00:17:04,992 --> 00:17:06,827
he was always there.

252
00:17:08,395 --> 00:17:10,163
We were both empty,

253
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:13,400
and I guess, looking back,

254
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:16,070
that’s why
we had nothing to hide.

255
00:17:16,136 --> 00:17:17,537
( Sighs )

256
00:17:21,642 --> 00:17:25,246
Sometimes I wonder
what he’s doing.

257
00:17:35,189 --> 00:17:37,224
I just wish I...

258
00:17:37,291 --> 00:17:38,959
Could see him again.

259
00:17:57,511 --> 00:17:58,479
( Sighs )

260
00:18:00,447 --> 00:18:01,481
That’s it.

261
00:18:01,548 --> 00:18:04,418
All I want now is to see gyro.

262
00:18:05,853 --> 00:18:08,789
I don’t care about ants,

263
00:18:08,856 --> 00:18:11,425
humans, cash, or countries,

264
00:18:11,492 --> 00:18:14,061
not anymore.

265
00:18:15,128 --> 00:18:17,464
♪

266
00:18:17,531 --> 00:18:18,565
Just go.

267
00:18:18,632 --> 00:18:21,168
The centipedes are gone.

268
00:18:21,235 --> 00:18:24,271
Don’t you still
have stuff to do?

269
00:18:26,373 --> 00:18:29,877
Ikalgo: First I wanna know
why you opened those two doors.

270
00:18:29,943 --> 00:18:31,344
Welfin: Hmm?

271
00:18:31,411 --> 00:18:35,115
Oh. Those weaklings wanted
the treasure in the back,

272
00:18:35,182 --> 00:18:36,450
so I let them in.

273
00:18:40,554 --> 00:18:43,290
Don’t worry.
They’re not a threat.

274
00:18:43,357 --> 00:18:46,894
I was watching you and blo
on the monitor,

275
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:51,064
and I told them to pass
while you were on the way back.

276
00:18:56,170 --> 00:18:58,105
( Ikalgo sobbing )

277
00:19:01,842 --> 00:19:05,913
I’m a coward! ( Sobbing )

278
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:08,014
Welfin: That’s all.

279
00:19:10,117 --> 00:19:13,053
Once I saw
that you couldn’t finish blo,

280
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:16,056
I figured you’d
be an easy target,

281
00:19:16,123 --> 00:19:19,460
but now I see I was wrong.

282
00:19:19,526 --> 00:19:21,828
( Sighs )

283
00:19:22,996 --> 00:19:24,931
( Sighs )

284
00:19:24,998 --> 00:19:26,566
You go ahead.

285
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:28,435
I’m way too tired.

286
00:19:28,502 --> 00:19:30,037
Ikalgo: One last question.

287
00:19:30,103 --> 00:19:31,271
Welfin: Huh?

288
00:19:31,338 --> 00:19:35,075
Ikalgo: Did you see
a woman in the palace?

289
00:19:35,142 --> 00:19:36,343
Welfin: A woman?

290
00:19:38,011 --> 00:19:40,113
Well, might not be her,

291
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:42,249
but the guards caught one,

292
00:19:42,316 --> 00:19:44,485
a human woman
they put inside a cocoon.

293
00:19:44,551 --> 00:19:47,087
( Ikalgo gasps )
Do you know where she is now?

294
00:19:47,154 --> 00:19:50,391
Welfin: Just take
the elevator up, and turn left.

295
00:19:50,457 --> 00:19:52,459
It’ll be the room at the end.

296
00:19:53,894 --> 00:19:55,963
They called it number one.

297
00:19:56,029 --> 00:19:57,097
( Ikalgo sighs )

298
00:19:57,164 --> 00:19:58,332
Thanks a lot!

299
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:02,302
( Welfin laughs )

300
00:20:02,369 --> 00:20:04,104
Ikalgo: What’s so funny?

301
00:20:04,171 --> 00:20:07,408
( Welfin laughs )

302
00:20:08,675 --> 00:20:11,311
I was just thinking,
I didn’t know

303
00:20:11,378 --> 00:20:15,315
that telling the truth
felt so good.

304
00:20:15,382 --> 00:20:16,383
Ikalgo: Hmm.

305
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:22,022
Narrator:
Welfin had spent his life

306
00:20:22,089 --> 00:20:25,125
unable to trust himself
or others.

307
00:20:25,192 --> 00:20:29,530
Telling ikalgo the location of
the woman he was searching for

308
00:20:29,596 --> 00:20:33,200
was the first time he had
ever opened up to someone,

309
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:36,303
spoken from the heart,
and told the truth.

310
00:21:04,565 --> 00:21:06,500
( Fluid sloshing)

311
00:21:12,372 --> 00:21:14,307
♪

312
00:21:25,152 --> 00:21:27,087
( Singing in Japanese )

